title: The Strange Love of Molly Louvain (1932) Ann Dvorak
description:
Fast-paced and sexy piece about a lady who uses her sex appeal to get ahead in the world, then it all comes crashing down around her. Ann Dvorak made this the same year she made Scarface, and the two have somewhat the same atmosphere - you notice many of her endearing mannerisms - also that she can really play the piano.

In segmented mpg format, plays in VLC.
